title: Grupo Aeroportuario passenger traffic up 9.8% in June
text:
Air and Travel · 
Grupo   2015 show total terminal passengers in the 12 Mexico-based airports increased 9.8 percent compared to the same period of the previous year.The Montego Bay airport traffic increased 0.7 percent during the same period. Domestic passenger traffic presented an 11.8 percent increase in the Mexican airports, while international passenger traffic increased 6.2 percent.The inclusion of Montego Bay contributed 306 thousand passengers to GAP´s airport network during the month of June.Grupo Aeroportuario del PacÃ­fico, S.A.B. de C.V. operates 12 airports throughout Mexico´s Pacific region, including the major cities of Guadalajara and Tijuana, the four tourist destinations of Puerto Vallarta, Los Cabos, La Paz and Manzanillo, and six other mid-sized cities: Hermosillo, Guanajuato, Morelia, Aguascalientes, Mexicali and Los Mochis.
